===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|こと|alt=箏:Japanese&nbsp;zither}}

{{IPAfont|⟨ko<sub>2</sub>to<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/kətə/}} → {{IPAchar|/koto/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=こと|-}}, attested in the three major literature works of the {{w|Nara period}}: the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' (712 {{CE}}), the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' (720 {{CE}}), and the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' (''c.'' 759 {{CE}}).<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|18|1435}}, text [https://web.archive.org/web/20230830001229/http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man18Yo.html#4135 here]</ref>

Possibly derived from a compound of elements {{compound|ja|sort=こと|木|tr1=ko|t1=[[tree]], [[wood]]|pos1=combining form|音|tr2=oto|t2=[[sound]]}}, with the additional medial ''o'' dropped by [[haplology]].

